For the Egyptians women, men enjoy sixty percent more opportunities for “leadership in the main occupations”.60 Additionally, Egyptian women spend 70% more time on unpaid work than men do: whilst men spend 35 total minutes a day on unpaid work, women adduce about five and a half hours.61 Source: A collage representing Egypt’s CEDAW representation at the UN headquarters, Mina Abozaglo, October 2019
